body.description: MAINGEAR IGNITION 1200W 80 Plus Platinum ATX Fully Modular Power Supply Made for gamers with an aggressive design and replaceable side decals to personalize the look of your system. A massive 100 Amp single rail designed with power hungry GPUs in mind and consistently provides reliable power even during heavy conditions. Run your PC in complete silence with ECO Mode, which deactivates the fan until a higher load and temperature is achieved. reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on May 12, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Excellent value power supply. Excellent warranty. Recommended by Microcenter staff.
reviews.reviewText: This power supply is a rebranded FSP Hydro PTM Pro 1200W. Definitely not the bottom of the barrel stuff, but the cables are a little stiff and not mesh braided. It's quiet, performs well and is much more affordable than the "big" name brands. My friend is using the 1000W version with no issues and I recently upgraded to the 1200W in anticipation of the RTX 4000 series graphics cards to be announced later this year. Will update within the year if anything changes.

reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Bought it at microcenter and havent had any issues
reviews.reviewText: Its been about 2.5 years since i've had the GPU now and i still have yet to have a single issue regarding this power supply. all my components get the power they need and i don't think i can exactly note that it has a loud fan. reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 28, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Power supply failure after 4 months.
reviews.reviewText: Happy I got the warranty. Power supply worked great until one morning I walked in and saw a blue flashing light next to a lightning bolt symbol on my PC case. No matter what I did it wouldn’t power on. Already got a new PSU to ensure it was a PSU failure and indeed it was.
¡cuidado! Ya que leí con detalle la descripción de la fuente que adquirí, pero me enviaron una de menor potencia
